window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>The J. G. Randall Distinguished Professor of History at the University of Illinois and associate editor of <i>North and South</i> magazine, Bruce Levine presents a gripping chronicle of the cultural and economic upheaval the South experienced during and after the Civil War. Drawing upon a treasure trove of diaries, letters, newspaper articles, and government documents, Levine offers a unique perspective on the old South's demise through the voices of those who lived through the conflict.</p>"; 
